 <title>Extraordinary fruits of openness</title>
 <link>http://www.alexstanhope.com/blog/fun/177/extraordinary-fruits-openness</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;The value of open source software is much talked about, both in terms of the direct and indirect returns to those that give their time to its construction and those that build composite services upon it.  Really interesting things happen when we stop associating open source with lines of code.&lt;/p&gt;
